  "prompt": "Is \"sher\" (\u0936\u0947\u0930) a lion or a tiger?",
  "response": "In Hindi, the word \"\u0936\u0947\u0930\" (sher) typically refers to a lion. However, it can sometimes be ambiguously used to refer to a tiger due to regional variations in usage. To minimize confusion, it's best to use more specific terms if the context requires clarity:\n\n- Lion: \u0936\u0947\u0930 (sher)\n- Tiger: \u092c\u093e\u0918 (bagh) or \u092c\u092c\u0930 \u0936\u0947\u0930 (babar sher, to specifically indicate a tiger)",
